{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17411384","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17411384"},"attributes":{"position":6,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260986"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260986"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12530"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17475114","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17475114"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:29:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:29:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12530"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1260986"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T06:24:33+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T07:02:58+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":13,"questionsAnswered":0,"marksTotal":0,"marksAttainable":0,"marksAttempted":0,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T06:25:33+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"12530","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12530"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.5,0.06,0.01,0.19]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5029"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"50071"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5029","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5029"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12530"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"35347"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"41"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2544"},{"type":"tags","id":"2790"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"13217"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8351"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13775"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16846"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"50071","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/50071"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA newborn boy is transferred to the neonatal intensive care unit as he is known to have a congenital cardiac lesion from his antenatal ultrasound. He has oxygen saturations in the 70s and appears cyanotic. His antenatal report states that he has transposition of the great arteries.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe cardiologist asks you to consider how this may have occurred embryologically.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is true regarding the normal embryological development of the great vessels?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The truncus arteriosus and truncus pulmonosis develop into the aorta and pulmonary trunk, respectively","The truncus arteriosus divides in a spiral pattern to form the aorta and pulmonary trunk","The aorta and pulmonary vessels develop from the first aortic arch","The aortic arch forms in the third trimester of pregnancy","The aorta connects to the right ventricle and the pulmonary trunk connects to the left ventricle"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring embryological development, the \u003Cstrong\u003Etruncus arteriosus\u003C/strong\u003E initially forms a single outflow tract from the heart. This common trunk must then divide to form the separate aorta and pulmonary trunk. The division occurs in a spiral pattern, which results in the normal anatomical arrangement of the aorta and pulmonary arteries. Failure of this spiral division can lead to transposition of the great arteries.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is no embryological structure called the \u003Cstrong\u003Etruncus pulmonosis\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Efirst aortic arch\u003C/strong\u003E largely regresses, with remnants contributing to the maxillary artery. It does not give rise to the aorta or pulmonary vessels.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eaortic arch\u003C/strong\u003E develops much earlier than the third trimester, forming during the first 8 weeks of gestation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn the normal heart, the \u003Cstrong\u003Eaorta connects to the left ventricle, while the pulmonary trunk connects to the right ventricle\u003C/strong\u003E. Transposition of the great arteries involves abnormal positioning of these vessels.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Congenital cardiac lesions develop due to errors in embryological development","Understanding embryology ensures a sound understanding of why pathology develops antenatally"],"references":["Khalid N, Bordoni B. Embryology, Great Vessel. [Updated 2022 May 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2022 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK545254/","Embryological development of the CVS, https://simplemed.co.uk/subjects/cardiovascular/embryology-of-the-cvs"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"35347"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12530"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"35347","links":{"self":"https://app.